<p><em class="focus">TÄTÄ SIVUA OLLAAN KÄÄNTÄMÄSSÄ SUOMEKSI.</em></p>

<p>Numerals are words that tell how many things an expression is referring to. They are divided into cardinal numerals, ordinal numerals and collective numerals. Cardinal numerals are words such as <em class="lg_mat">okta, guokte, golbma</em> (one, two, three). <em class="focus"> Ordinal numerals are adjectives:</em> <em class="lg_mat">vuosttaš, nubbi, goalmmát</em> (first, second, third). <em class="focus">Collective numerals are nouns:</em> <em class="lg_mat">guovttis, golmmas, njealjis</em> (two people, three people, four people). </p>

